# skillskit.dev site — environment variables
#
# All variables prefixed PUBLIC_ are inlined into the client bundle at
# build time by Astro/Vite. Anything secret (no customer data is
# involved on this static site, but still) must NOT use the PUBLIC_
# prefix. This file is checked in; .env is gitignored.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# PostHog Cloud — product analytics.
#
# When PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY is set, Base.astro injects the PostHog JS
# snippet and src/lib/analytics.ts's `track()` calls start firing.
# Without the key, analytics no-op cleanly (useful in local dev and on
# previews where you don't want to pollute the real project).
#
# Grab the key from https://us.posthog.com/project/settings → Project
# API Key (it's a "public" project key, safe to ship in the client).
#
# On Amplify: App settings → Environment variables → add
# PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY (scope to "main" if you don't want previews to
# send events).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY=
PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST=https://us.i.posthog.com
